As you may already know (or not), this can be tested directly. The issue is that the following configuration does not work for applying settings to all direct children in the mega menu:

`/en/ghg-knowledge-hub: {
  hideChildrenFromNavigation: false,
}`
Instead, you need to explicitly define each child route individually, like this:

`
'/en/ghg-knowledge-hub/lulucf': {
  hideChildrenFromNavigation: false,
}
`
This approach is not dynamic—every time an editor adds a new page, the configuration must be manually updated.

With the latest solution proposed, this implementation of the routes is possible: [this PR](https://github.com/eea/volto-eea-website-policy/pull/108). This will check the children too.

